{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 11:01:49.885352", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission accepted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"dhcp_server\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"dhcp_missing_subnet\"]\n\nDiagnosis recap (concise):\n- Host host_2_1_1_1 has no IPv4 address despite link and switch being up.\n- router_dist_2_1 is advertising/hosting 10.2.1.0/24 (gateway 10.2.1.1); routing is functional.\n- dhcp_server config lacks a subnet declaration/pool for 10.2.1.0/24, so DHCP requests from host_2 cannot be granted leases.\n- Impact: host_2 and other hosts in 10.2.1.0/24 that rely on DHCP cannot obtain IPs and are unreachable.\n\nRecommended remediation (next steps you can apply):\n1. Add a DHCP subnet declaration to /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf for 10.2.1.0/24, for example:\n   subnet 10.2.1.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 {\n     range 10.2.1.10 10.2.1.100;\n     option routers 10.2.1.1;\n     option domain-name-servers 10.200.0.2;\n   }\n2. Restart or reload the DHCP service (e.g., systemctl restart isc-dhcp-server) and verify no errors in dhcpd logs.\n3. Confirm host_2 obtains a lease (check ip addr, dhclient logs or run dhclient on host_2), and verify reachability to DNS and servers.\n4. If DHCP requests are relayed by router_dist_2_1, verify ip helper/relay configuration so DHCPDISCOVER reaches dhcp_server.\n5. Optionally, collect DHCP logs and packet captures during repro for verification.\n\nIf you want, I can generate the exact dhcpd.conf snippet tailored to your existing pool ranges and restart commands for your DHCP server OS.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2155, "output_tokens": 421, "total_tokens": 2576, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
